      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw F1717 applicability domain",
      "description": "Model applies exclusively to non-cannulated titanium-alloy pedicle screws with nominal diameter 7.0–8.0 mm and pitch 2.75–3.25 mm, loaded under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol with a 35 mm offset arm. Excludes cannulated variants, dynamic fatigue loading, and screws outside the stated dimensional envelope."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "F1717 compression-bending operating envelope",
      "description": "Applied compressive displacement: 0–50 mm at 25 mm/min crosshead speed. Offset arm length: 35 ± 0.5 mm. Construct axial alignment: ±2° of nominal. Ambient temperature: 20–25 °C. Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI, UTS 930–970 MPa, yield 860–900 MPa. Bone surrogate: 40 pcf rigid polyurethane foam per ASTM F1839. All parameters verified against laboratory records prior to model comparison."
    }
  },
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/sa/compression-bending-mrl5",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global variance-based sensitivity analysis for F1717 compression-bending FEA",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-order indices computed via quasi-Monte Carlo sampling (N=8192 model evaluations) across seven uncertain inputs: titanium Young's modulus (±5%), screw thread root radius (±0.05 mm), polyurethane foam modulus (±15%), contact friction coefficient (±0.08), offset arm length (±0.5 mm), crosshead displacement rate (±2 mm/min), and mesh density (±20% element count). Dominant factors for construct stiffness QoI were foam modulus (S_T=0.41) and screw thread root radius (S_T=0.29); for yield force, titanium Young's modulus (S_T=0.38) and thread root radius (S_T=0.33) dominated. Interaction terms accounted for less than 12% of total variance across all QoIs."
  },
